Re: How divisible are bitcoins and other market/economic questions

Bitcointalk

2010-02-06 23:25:53 UTC - [11]Original Post

   Eventually at most only 21 million coins for 6.8 billion people in the
   world if it really gets huge.
   But donʼt worry, there are another 6 decimal places that arenʼt shown,
   for a total of 8 decimal places internally.  It shows 1.00 but
   internally itʼs 1.00000000.  If thereʼs massive deflation in the
   future, the software could show more decimal places.
   If it gets tiresome working with small numbers, we could change where
   the display shows the decimal point.  Same amount of money, just
   different convention for where the ","ʼs and "."ʼs go.  e.g. moving the
   decimal place 3 places would mean if you had 1.00000 before, now it
   shows it as 1,000.00.
